               <p>JOHN WADE. I am a carpenter. On the 25th of June I was near the prosecutor's shop, and saw the prisoner -I watched him, and he passed me three or four times; he then went to the shop door, and took the brushes from the post, put them under his apron, and walked away; I went, and took him about a hundred yards off- I found the brushes on him.</p>
